Steps to install HoneyDB:

1. Run "build.sh"

2. Inside LXC Container named "db-server", do following:
    (i) Login as a root using mysql-client
    (ii) Install "MariaDB Audit Plugin" using following command:
        --> INSTALL PLUGIN server_audit SONAME 'server_audit';
    (iii) Change the content of "/etc/mysql/my.cnf" with available "my.cnf" in this repo
    (iv) Comment out the "bind-address = 127.0.0.1" part in "/etc/mysql/mariadb.conf.d/50-server.cnf" file, so that root user can be remotely accessible.
    (v) Restart your mysql service using "service mysql restart"
    **Now all the logs will be logged in /var/log/mysql/audit.log file in Container**

3. Add port forwarding rules in your HOST system using following commands of IPTABLES:
    Notation: Y- HOST System
              Z- Container System

    -->iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -p tcp -i eth0 -d Y.Y.Y.Y --dport 3306 -j DNAT --to Z.Z.Z.Z:3306
    -->iptables -A FORWARD -p tcp -i eth0 -d Z.Z.Z.Z --dport 3306 -j ACCEPT

4. Happy Hacking!!
